  "prompt": "Why is Manaphy anxious in Pok\u00e9mon Ranger and the Temple of the Sea?",
  "response": "In *Pok\u00e9mon Ranger and the Temple of the Sea*, Manaphy is initially anxious due to its unique circumstances and the challenges it faces. Here are the key reasons for its anxiety:\n\n1. **Separation from its Parent**: Manaphy was separated from its parent, Phione or Manaphy, which naturally causes distress. It hatched from an Egg in the care of a human, leaving it vulnerable and unsure of its place in the world.\n\n2. **Protection from Hunters**: Manaphy is being pursued by pirates, including the antagonist Phantom, who want to exploit its powers. This constant threat makes Manaphy fearful and anxious about its safety.\n\n3. **Responsibility as the Prince of the Sea**: Manaphy is revealed to be the prince of the Sea Temple and holds the key to unlocking its mysteries. This responsibility weighs heavily on it, especially since it is still young and inexperienced.\n\n4. **Unfamiliar Environment**: Manaphy is out of its natural habitat for much of the story, which adds to its anxiety. It relies on Ash, May, and the others to guide and protect it, but it still feels out of place in the human world.\n\nAs the story progresses, Manaphy grows more confident and learns to trust its companions, helping it overcome its fears and fulfill its destiny.",
